Elytra 1.7 times as long as wide; omoplates and postbasal impression absent. Setation whitish and brownish, forming rather distinct transverse bands / spots (
Fig. 199
), uniformly short and appressed; setae coarsely hairy to scaly (linear), truncate apically, evenly ordered and sparse (surface clearly visible); erect tactile setae absent.
